<H1>&nbsp;</H1>
<H1><FONT color="mediumblue">Singular Value Decomposition <font size="3"> Contd.</font> </FONT></H1>
</CENTER>

<UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL><UL>
       <LI><FONT size=5>Diagonal of <font color="#FF0000"> S</font> contains singular values of
        <font color="#FF0000"> A</font> in the descending order. </font></LI>
       <BR><BR>
       <LI><FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">A</font> is formed from LSI as follows:</FONT></LI>
<p align="left">
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5 color="#FF0000">A = U<sup>S</sup> * S<sup>S</sup> * V<sup>ST</sup></FONT>
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">U<sup>S</sup></font> - derived from<font color="#FF0000"> U</font> removing all but the<font color="#FF0000"> s</font> columns </FONT>
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">S<sup>S</sup></font> - derived from <font color="#FF0000"> S</font> removing all but the largest
       <font color="#FF0000"> s</font> singular values </FONT>
       <BR><BR>
       <FONT size=5><font color="#FF0000">V<sup>sT</sup></font> - derived from <font color="#FF0000">V<sup>T</sup></font> removing all but the
       <font color="#FF0000"> s</font> corresponding rows </FONT>
</UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL></UL>

